Transmission Grid Expansion and System Reliability  Conferences
=20

May 21-25, 2001, Denver, Colorado



Overview
=20

The conferences focus on the Regulatory Issues and Pricing of  Transmission=
.=20
The conferences also have a strong focus on enabling transmission =20
technologies. These advanced transmission technologies promise market =20
participants speed and flexibility towards achieving their goals of=20
enhancing  system capacity, responding to price incentives and increasing=
=20
system  reliability.

In the post FERC 2000 era, the industry participants are  looking for clear=
=20
guidelines on regulation and pricing. A well defined  regulatory and pricin=
g=20
structure would allow them to pursue their business  models without=20
compromising the reliability of the national electric grid. The  crisis in=
=20
California reinforces the need for these clear guidelines. While the  rules=
=20
of the game are still not as clear as many would like it and while there  a=
re=20
vast differences in approach in different regions, some areas of consensus =
=20
have emerged among market participants and regulators. The industry experts=
 =20
participating in this conference provide a focus group for identifying area=
s=20
of  consensus. The conference participants will also be able to form opinio=
ns=20
on  areas where regulation is not addressing the issues and need to be=20
addressed.  Participants will also come away with a good appreciation of wh=
at=20
is  technologically feasible to meet their business goals.

The brochure for the conferences and associated workshop is  attached=20
herewith. The registration information is included in the brochure.  Please=
=20
print the brochure and fax the registration form back to us.
=20




